==English==
===Adjective phrase===
'''in the closet''' (''not [[comparable]]'')

#(''colloquial'') Not open about one's [[homosexuality]] or [[bisexuality]].
#(''colloquial''; ''by extension from sense 1'') Not open about some feature of one's life; ''often construed with'' [[about]].
#:She's '''in the closet''' about her gambling addiction.
#:''or'', She's '''in the''' gambling-addiction '''closet'''.

